30s hit different! 
.

When I tell you the best compliment ever is when people are shocked that I’m 30. Yes out looking like I’m still 21 at times 😝

I enjoy being FINE AF at 30 but also being a better human being at 30 too.

✨Monday Mood✨
Could you imagine a month ago, I was on the floor at my parents house crying my eyes out…no right lol. I realize now that I needed that cry, I needed to feel uncertain and I needed to feel so heavy, that I had no choice but to surrender to God’s will.
.
.
I say all of that to say, I’m so grateful for my rainy days because I know I’m being planted for a greater purpose. After that day I felt internally PRETTY. It really does start inside out. So when I hear now, “You look so pretty and happy” I give a simple Thank You and know that it comes from a deeper healed place. 
.
.
Happy Monday!

Long Post Alert lol
.
.
7 years of life was dedicated and shaped around auditioning, and being a part of this team. I had so many emotions about my reunion from excitement, nerves, eagerness and even uncertainty. Grizz Girls was such a major chapter in my life, where I experience the highest of highs, and the lowest of lows! In the end that experience shaped me as a dancer, as a professional, and certainly as a woman. 
The weekend was filled with so much love and support because we are truly a sisterhood. 
Thank you @terrannoir for cultivating a weekend experience, that I will never forget.
.
.
But this weekend really was a release because of @tamtamrox! You have shaped me in so many ways and I’m so thankful for every second we spoke! My heart needed it, my spirit needed, the dancer trying her damn hardest to be seen by you needed it. The tough love you gave me, is full circle and I love you for it. @tamtamrox you hands down are still one of my biggest inspiration! Thank you! 
.
.
Of course to my parents @janel_goods @phatmerv88! To dance on court again and you guys doing the same thing, was the highlight of being back! I love you deeply for the encouragement and always telling me my best is good enough! I love y’all! 
.
. #reels #instagood #grizz #memphis #grizzgirls #jamorant #atl #dancer #love #fyp #viral #blackgirlmagic #tgoods8 #trinicagoods

Happy International Women’s Day!
.
.
Transparent Moment (cause we love those don’t we)
I have no clue what this season of my life is…I’m extremely uncomfortable right now. For the longest I’ve never felt truly seen as myself and dance was my escape. But dance has been rough lately, reminding myself of my worth has been hard lately. It’s just been hard! 
But I give myself grace…to say I don’t know and that being the answer for now! 
So shoutout to all the women who just simply don’t know in this moment. I pray for our strength, resilience and patience with ourselves. 
Love Trinica!

•Virtual Private Sessions•

No two people are the same. Everyone has their own unique ways about them. So I always cater to each session for what the client needs.
.
.
I’ve had the pleasure of working with @_kiarareed and we STRETCH!! I love to incorporate her son to help during sessions and he loves it ( he loves making her feel the burn lol). It’s a great way for me to practice on verbally articulating the skill and allowing them to bond. 
.
.
Kiara really is the definition of “PUSHING THROUGH”! I will tell her to rest and she will say No, I’m good! Let’s keep going! So we are working on her listening to her body and knowing when to rest. She has been a pleasure to work it. Let’s keep it going!

When your sissy comes in town and she has two days off… you bribe her to braid your hair 😂😂😂! Love you @kaylamarie.j 
.

My hair already has a custom color, so it wasn’t like we just went to the store picked up packs and started braiding. I told @kaylamarie.j I wanted my braids to match the color layout of my hair. Y’all my girl got to pulling and blending together different packs of hair to match my hair EXACTLY! 
.
.

- Industry 101 Recap -
.
It’s officially been 1 week since our final showcase and I’m really still trying process everything. 
.
.
30 days, 5/6 days a week, 8 hours of training & living in a whole new city/state. Talk about a mental & physical mind fuck.
This process really challenged me to get out of my head and into my body. Other days I had to get out of my body and get into my head. But what a beautiful experience. I legit pushed beyond what I told myself I could do and more. The additional knowledge and skills learned were top tier. I know I’m Ready FOR ALL THE ROOMS, I want to be in.
